Package MatrixPackage

Record Class Indexes

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
MatrixPackage.Indexes
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Indexes>
public record Indexes(int row, int column) extends Record implements Comparable<Indexes>
This is a record representing the index of a matrix. It has an int row and int column, which represent the dimentions of the index.
Author:
Vidyut Veedgav

    • areDiagonal

      public boolean areDiagonal()
      Determines if the index is along the matrix diagonal by checking if the row and column fields are equal. If they are, it means that the index lies on the diagonal path of the matrix.
      Returns:
      true if the row is equal to the column; false otherwise.
